race.comment: READY TO RUSH (4) let down well when asked to score a tough win on debut last time out over 1100m at Cootamundra. In a good stable and should take this next step. BLANC DE NOIR (1) raced on the speed but was found wanting in the closing stages over this distance at Kembla recently. Won't find this as tough and with a few key gear changes today can do a lot better. ETERNAL EMBER (7) led from the outset to record a brave win on debut over 1065m at the Wagga Riverside circuit last start. Should be competitive despite tackling some better types this time. COMMANDORO (8) doesn't win out of turn but is nicely weighted and appeals on an each-way basis. GHIELMI (2) has been racing well at the provincials and will be hard to beat coming back in grade.
